eration against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Hold Until Reminder Time · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1938,280],"id":"59974520-30fc-d9d8-7989-aa33951c2f28","name":"Note: Send Confirmation (Slack)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Propose Alternative Slots\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2262,880],"id":"97b346d2-9187-1dc7-acb7-5a09a0b26062","name":"Note: Propose Alternative Slots"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Hold Until Reminder Time\n\nPauses 1 hours — spacing calls to respect rate limits.\n\nNext: Send Reminder (Slack)","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3234,520],"id":"37f07b77-c754-f20b-744b-0ec169543bcd","name":"Note: Hold Until Reminder Time"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Reminder (Slack)\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Fingerprint for Idempotency · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3558,520],"id":"a3ec54f8-3cdf-9a2b-12af-97aa92e98820","name":"Note: Send Reminder (Slack)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fingerprint for Idempotency\n\nCustom JavaScript: Build a stable idempotency key per task (djb2 hash, no deps)\n\nNext: Drop Already-Processed Items","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3882,520],"id":"665ec1d7-0126-b9f6-279b-dba5d6974f42","name":"Note: Fingerprint for Idempotency"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Drop Already-Processed Items\n\nCross-execution dedupe: remembers keys it has processed before and drops repeats — the idempotency guard.\n\nNext: Enrich with Reference Data","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4206,520],"id":"cc201b70-2f40-431a-90e0-522658038e5d","name":"Note: Drop Already-Processed Items"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Enrich with Reference Data\n\nGET https://enrichment.example.com/v2/lookup — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nPorts: ①→ Fold In Enrichment Fields · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4530,520],"id":"51827b53-1c0f-7aa0-b1fa-100c187f529e","name":"Note: Enrich with Reference Data"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fold In Enrichment Fields\n\nShapes the item: writes `enrichedAt`, `enrichmentSource`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Load Previous Snapshot","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4854,520],"id":"8660aae6-901c-1551-61bc-ca7594444e96","name":"Note: Fold In Enrichment Fields"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Load Previous Snapshot\n\ngoogleSheets — `read` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Compute Drift vs Snapshot · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5178,520],"id":"7b2c0454-3720-9ec9-3492-57261a27379c","name":"Note: Load Previous Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Compute Drift vs Snapshot\n\nCustom JavaScript: Compare current metrics with the previous snapshot\n\nNext: Summarize Run Stats","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5502,520],"id":"17bb7c2e-994f-727f-59e0-3788e9edf5f0","name":"Note: Compute Drift vs Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Summarize Run Stats\n\nShapes the item: writes `runAt`, `itemCount`, `status`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5826,520],"id":"40648121-5007-441f-cfd3-e9c7169c509a","name":"Note: Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Send Summary to Slack · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6150,520],"id":"1f6ff176-f05e-b886-c289-987ad8e732b4","name":"Note: Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6474,520],"id":"08425f17-77f9-25b9-c0d8-3d4c36d119e0","name":"Note: Send Summary to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5826,1540],"id":"76cab348-6ffd-f711-caa0-f32c6d025df4","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\nNext: Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6150,1540],"id":"2e75b714-5acd-4c45-5dbb-7c242908b924","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6474,1540],"id":"9d39a2f2-d751-b0f0-572e-381bd2f5e09b","name":"Note: Park in Dead-Letter Queue"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Onboard new customers with Jira and Slack with instant alerts\n\n**Pattern:** Onboarding Sequence · **Level:** Production · **Trigger:** Webhook\n\n## What it does\nOnboard new customers with Jira and Slack with instant alerts. It fires the moment an external system calls its webhook.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual task routing is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nReceive Inbound Webhook → Stamp & Shape Task → Payload Valid? → Check Calendar Availability → Slot Free? → Create Calendar Event → Send Confirmation (Slack) → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to onboarding sequence without manual effort\n- Anyone automating task routing in software development\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Keeps your systems in sync\n- Removes copy-paste errors\n- Improves response time\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google OAuth2; Google OAuth2 / service account; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"8f2d71df-0864-f35c-b5be-843d5492c1c8","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-260],"id":"043e2748-59b6-aad1-45de-aa2cfa3990f3","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## ⏱ Rate limiting\n\nWork is batched and spaced with Wait so provider quotas aren't tripped. If you hit 429s, lower the batch size or raise the wait — throughput drops, reliability rises.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-260],"id":"1b073d6b-19fb-3d98-192d-101b02af6b5d","name":"⏱ Rate limiting"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🔐 Security\n\nNever trust inbound payloads: the webhook path is unguessable. Add header auth or IP allow-listing for defense in depth. Secrets live in n8n credentials — never in node parameters.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-260],"id":"bfc0b588-10a9-9296-d9d3-9399caa33ad1","name":"🔐 Security"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your task routing process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1030,-260],"id":"4a3cc135-dafb-cc1f-2708-d858cd0b932f","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"Receive Inbound Webhook":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp & Shape Task","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp & Shape Task":{"main":[[{"node":"Payload Valid?","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Payload Valid?":{"main":[[{"node":"Check Calendar Availability","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Record Rejected Input","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Check Calendar Availability":{"main":[[{"node":"Slot Free?","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Slot Free?":{"main":[[{"node":"Create Calendar Event","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Propose Alternative Slots","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Create Calendar Event":{"main":[[{"node":"Send Confirmation (Slack)","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Send Confirmation (Slack)":{"main":[[{"node":"Hold Until Reminder Time","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Hold Until Reminder Time":{"main":[[{"node":"Send Reminder (Slack)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Send Reminder (Slack)":{"main":[[{"node":"Fingerprint for Idempotency","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fingerprint for Idempotency":{"main":[[{"node":"Drop Already-Processed Items","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Drop Already-Processed Items":{"main":[[{"node":"Enrich with Reference Data","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Enrich with Reference Data":{"main":[[{"node":"Fold In Enrichment Fields","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fold In Enrichment Fields":{"main":[[{"node":"Load Previous Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Load Previous Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Compute Drift vs Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Compute Drift vs Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Summarize Run Stats","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Summarize Run Stats":{"main":[[{"node":"Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Append Audit Row (Google Sheets)":{"main":[[{"node":"Send Summary to Slack","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Capture Failure Context":{"main":[[{"node":"Escalate Failure to Slack","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Escalate Failure to Slack":{"main":[[{"node":"Park in Dead-Letter Queue","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Propose Alternative Slots":{"main":[[],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Send Summary to Slack":{"main":[[],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]}},"active":false,"settings":{"executionOrder":"v1"},"meta":{"templateCredsSetupCompleted":false},"tags":[],"pinData":{},"versionId":"5bb9f235-13b8-441b-8cb6-ebcb220a4e8e","id":"FDX08413"}